{
  "text": "Therefore, our study does not fully comply with the previous report [CITATION_1] . This dis crepancy in the sub unit variation may be due to: (a) variation in the time of collection of blood, (b) area and intensity of burns (Table I ) and (c) number of patients. The re li ability of our data lies in the larger sample size. Software analysis of the LDH-gel scans reveals a significant increase in the sera TLDH activity of patients compared with control values (P=0.05). This is in agreement with the previous reports where an ele vation in the sera TLDH activity of burns has been de monstrated [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
